Rating: 4
Terrific stew - and I'm not usually a fan of beef stew. I made a number of alterations to the basic recipe. First, I'm not a big fan of onions, so I cut the onion volume in half. I added about a pound of chopped mushrooms and a lot of garlic (we love garlic): about 4 tablespoons of chopped garlic in oil (milder than fresh cloves - would have used 3 medium gloves). I sauteed the beef first, added it to the slow cooker, and then sauteed the mushrooms, onions and garlic together and added them to the slow cooker. I reduced the liquid a little (because I was making it in a slow cooker) by pouring off some of the liquid in the canned tomatoes and cutting the wine to about 1 cup. The second time I made the recipe, I also added about half a teaspoon of chili flakes. About an hour before it was finished cooking in the slow cooker (8.5 hours at Low), I added a roughly chopped medium bulb of fennel as well as the carrots, because we prefer vegetables to be crisp-tender.

