Rating: 4
Check your Hoisin sauce! Lee Kum Kee brand has sugar as the first ingredient (10g sugar per TBS!); it's a black syrupy, tasteless sludge. Whole Foods brand has soy sauce as the first ingredient, 3g sugar per TBS, and has tons of complex flavors. I suspect that explains some of the radically different results....

