Modifications: dredged the beef in flour first, halved the hoisin sauce, added slightly more wine and tomato sauce, and cut out the cornstarch. I was a little dubious about this recipe, particularly given others' comments, but it ended up being one of the best stews I've made. The hoisin sauce added more depth to the sauce than is normally found, and though it may have been slightly sweet, I thought the onions cut that nicely. I'm not sure I would add potatoes, because they seem a bit too heavy for the (surprisingly delicate) sauce. I would vote for either pearl onions or mushrooms.

