Rating: 3
I have made this recipe probably a dozen times now. Everyone loves it! I have my tweeked version all figured out and thought I'd share. I use 2 pounds natual stew beef, 2 pounds potatoes, and a package of mushrooms or 2-3 portobellos, and only 1/3 cup hoisin. Add the potatoes with the carrots. Add the mushrooms about 1/2 hour before finish. I use the amount of wine in the recipe and sometimes add a little more if needed. The wine and hoisin make the flavor of this stew. Rather that the recipe simmering instructions, I just let it simmer for about 2 hours. More, if I have the time. I usually don't need any cornstarch, but have used occasionally when I don't have time for more simmer. Enjoy!

