Rating: 4
Probably the best beef stew that I have ever had. I left the chuck roast in one piece (it falls apart anyway so don't bother cutting it into chunks) trimmed the excess fat, browned it really well on all sides and then put it in the slow cooker. Sauteed the onions and sliced carrots in the same pan along with some chopped garlic and then deglazed the pan with some of the wine; put that and the rest of the ingredients on top of the meat in the slow cooker on low for 8 hours. I did use one cup of wine and one cup of beef broth as some people suggested. The hoisin adds a depth of flavor that is just fantastic. One of the absolute best recipes ever!! :)

