Rating: 4
This dish can be fantastic or ordinary. What's the difference? Three easy elements: 1) Meat -- Use a better, lower-fat cut of meat than the suggested chuck, and cut the pieces smaller than the recipe suggests (you want chunks half the size of what the recipe calls for); 2) Marinade -- Before cooking the meat, marinate it for 20 minutes in the cabernet, and it'll taste worlds better; 3) Sauce -- If you use a little less meat than what this recipe calls for, the meat/sauce ratio is divine. I've made this dish multiple times, and when I've made it according to the recipe, I've found it average; when I've tweaked it as described here, I've found it exquisite.

