Rating: 4
I've made this twice now and learned that you should avoid the sweeter variety of hoisin sauce. The Kame brand is best, which has a pungent, non-sweet plummy taste. Also, the onions carmelize better if they are chopped very coarse. If you do these 2 things right, you can't go wrong with this recipe.

