Rating: 3
Very good, but like several others, did it with a twist - and did it all in less than an hour start to finish. Browned the beef - in batches -in a pressure cooker, then dumped in everything but the carrots (based on the group's comments, thought it might be too sweet). Brought to high pressure for 18 minutes, let the pressure drop naturally (about 10 minutes), and then thickened with flour-water mixture on the stove. This way, the meat was very tender (think tenderloin) but definately NOT stringy, and the sauce was silky smooth and delicious. Will make again the same way, but this time will add your suggestions of adding garlic and sauteed mushrooms. Will also serve with mashed potatoes. A great cold weather dish!

Rating: 3
