Wonderful flavor! I did read all the reviews before I made this. What a great service, am not sure I would have tried it without them so thank you all. I made the recipe as written, but I did take out the meat to do the onions and simmered a little longer than 45 minutes; also added button mushrooms along with the carrots, as suggested. Used my 4 qt. Scan Pan saucepot which was the perfect size. The comments about sweetness concerned me, as we don't even care for sugary sweet potato dishes, but that was definitely not a problem. It is a different kind of sweetness, and I can't think of a better way to say it. Not at all objectionableto us. Taste varies, so if you finish the stew and it tastes sweet to you, judiciously add salt. If it is not salty enough, it will taste sweet, and salt is hard to judge in it. Also, use the wine recommended. A less dry wine can really make a difference. Served with the horseradish potatoes. Yummy! This is an easy dish to make and IMO much better than the short ribs!

