Rating: 3
Best beef stew I've ever had. I skipped the carrots, since I don't like them, and added dried white mushrooms and dried shiitake mushrooms midway through cooking. I cooked about 3 hours on very low heat, and midway through, when I added the extra wine, I also added another 1/2 c of hoisin. I didn't need the cornstach as a thickener, and I thought the flavor was lovely--you can't tell it's hoisin, but it sure is good. I garnished with finely chopped scallions.

