Rating: 3
We thought this was a huge payoff for a minimal effort--must be the hoisin. We have a majority who hate to eat cooked carrots, so we just threw in a couple whole ones for the sweetness, making them easy to navigate around when serving. Then added button mushroom caps instead, which worked really well. Make sure you use a sufficiently large pot or you'll have a hard time browning the beef and onions. We had to switch pots after we realized our first choice was too small. It was wonderful with mashed potatoes the first night and great over egg noodles as leftovers.